{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2018/10/26/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"lukasz-madon/awesome-remote-job","categoryHTML":"<h2>Companies with \"remote DNA\"</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://careers.isostech.com/\">Isos Technology</a> - premier Atlassian Platinum &#x26; Enterprise Solution Partner, helping organizations solve complex development and business problems with the Atlassian tools.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T22:42:49.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vinta/awesome-python","categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://testandcode.com/\">Test and Code</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T17:44:12.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategy</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://petersengames.com/cthulhu-wars/\">Cthulhu Wars</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Cthulhu Wars is a fast-moving strategy game about the end of the world. You take the part of various monstrous aliens seeking to dominate the world. You can play as Great Cthulhu himself, or you can take charge of other factions, such as the slithering hordes of the Crawling Chaos, or the insane minions of the Yellow Sign.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/Q5jn_9sxJzHb9KTKKGq44t_k-3U=/fit-in/246x300/pic3527761.jpg\" alt=\"Cthulhu Wars game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2 - 8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">12</td>\n<td align=\"right\">90-120m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T17:39:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategy</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"http://anachronyboardgame.com/\">Anachrony</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Anachrony is a competitive Euro-style strategy game set in a post-apocalyptic world rebuilt along four different ideological Paths. The game is played through a series of turns called Eras, with past ones reachable through time travel later in the game. Players assume the roles of iconic leaders of the four Paths, striving not only for the supremacy and well-being of their people, but also their survival. After the fourth Era, an asteroid impact shakes Earth, threatening to destroy the World Capital, Earth’s last independent city. The Paths should prepare for the coming cataclysm, and when the time comes, take their part in evacuating the collapsing Capital. In the end, one of the Paths will be the new home to the reformed World Council, and lead humanity into a new future.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/SnpcIpaKXsWaMWsxf4-bZHDbSG0=/fit-in/246x300/pic3499707.jpg\" alt=\"Anachrony game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">1 - 4</td>\n<td align=\"right\">15</td>\n<td align=\"right\">30-120m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T17:39:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategy</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"http://www.eggrules.com/games/games-00-c/clockwork-wars/\">Clockwork Wars</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In Clockwork Wars each player commands a unique race of creatures in a tense war game set in a fantasy-steampunk universe. Take control of the calculating Purebreeds, the industrious Troglodytes, the mighty Rhinochs, or the proud Mongrels. Your goal is to vanquish your foes and accumulate the most victory points through nine turns of play. You earn points by fighting for control of territories that contain valuable natural resources. To win these battles, you need manpower gained by seizing villages and developing them into cities. Invest in research and discover astonishing new technologies, position your troops, research powerful discoveries, employ espionage, and conquer your enemies to win the game!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/7LucYPx8-t-0vMs6Rfhp_vzr2Y4=/fit-in/246x300/pic2355823.jpg\" alt=\"Clockwork Wars game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2 - 4</td>\n<td align=\"right\">13</td>\n<td align=\"right\">90-120m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T17:39:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>USENIX Security</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://enigma.usenix.org/sites/default/files/sec13_proceedings_interior.pdf#page=57\">Dowsing for overflows: a guided fuzzer to find buffer boundary violations, 2013</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T16:37:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>The others</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/488a/b1e313f5109153f2c74e3b5d86d41e9b4b71.pdf\">Hybrid fuzz testing: Discovering software bugs via fuzzing and symbolic execution, 2012</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T16:34:34.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>The others</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.computer.org/csdl/proceedings/iccsa/2008/3243/00/3243a019-abs.html\">Call-Flow Aware API Fuzz Testing for Security of Windows Systems, 2008</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T16:25:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>USENIX Security</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://softsec.kaist.ac.kr/~sangkilc/papers/rebert-usenixsec14.pdf\">Optimizing Seed Selection for Fuzzing, 2014</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T16:24:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>ArXiv (Fuzzing with Artificial Intelligence &#x26; Machine Learning)</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1809.01266\">Coverage-Guided Fuzzing for Deep Neural Networks, 2018</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T16:24:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>ArXiv (Fuzzing with Artificial Intelligence &#x26; Machine Learning)</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1711.04596\">Not all bytes are equal: Neural byte sieve for fuzzing, 2017</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T16:24:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cpuu/awesome-fuzzing","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>USENIX Security</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.usenix.org/system/files/conference/usenixsecurity12/sec12-final73.pdf\">Fuzzing with Code Fragments, 2012</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T16:17:31.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"unixorn/awesome-zsh-plugins","categoryHTML":"<h2>Themes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/rberenguel/rb-zsh-theme\">rb</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/rberenguel/rb-zsh-theme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2,\"repo\":\"rberenguel/rb-zsh-theme\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Powerline-styled ZSH theme based on <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/agnoster/3712874\">Agnoster</a>, optimized for <code>git</code> and solarized terminals. Requires a Powerline-compatible font.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T15:31:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"unixorn/awesome-zsh-plugins","categoryHTML":"<h2>Themes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Ottootto2010/funkyberlin-zsh-theme\">funkyberlin</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Ottootto2010/funkyberlin-zsh-theme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"Ottootto2010/funkyberlin-zsh-theme\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A colorful two-line theme with support for <code>git</code> and <code>svn</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T15:28:59.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Family</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Betrayal_at_House_on_the_Hill\">Betrayal at House on the Hill</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Players all begin as allies exploring a haunted house filled with dangers, traps, items, and omens.<br>\nAs players journey to new parts of the mansion, room tiles are chosen at random and placed on the game board.<br>\nEventually the \"haunt\" begins, one player usually \"betrays\" the others and takes the side of the ghosts, monsters, or other enemies, while the remaining players collaborate to defeat them.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/Les6nIiycIhjCX7kbUosXATygEc=/fit-in/246x300/pic828598.jpg\" alt=\"Betrayal at House on the Hill game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">3 - 6</td>\n<td align=\"right\">13</td>\n<td align=\"right\">60m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T14:19:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"glauberfc/awesome-react-hooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hooks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-intro.html\">Introducing Hooks</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T14:14:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"glauberfc/awesome-react-hooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hooks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-overview.html\">Hooks at a Glance</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T14:14:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"glauberfc/awesome-react-hooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hooks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-state.html\">Using the State Hook</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T14:14:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"glauberfc/awesome-react-hooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hooks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-effect.html\">Using the Effect Hook</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T14:14:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"glauberfc/awesome-react-hooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hooks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-rules.html\">Rules of Hooks</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T14:14:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"glauberfc/awesome-react-hooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hooks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-reference.html\">Hooks API Reference</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T14:14:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"glauberfc/awesome-react-hooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Hooks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-faq.html\">Hooks FAQ</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T14:14:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Family</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dixit_(card_game)\">Dixit</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Using a deck of cards illustrated with dreamlike images, players select cards that match a title suggested by the \"storyteller\", and attempt to guess which card the \"storyteller\" selected.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7b/Dixitgame.jpg/200px-Dixitgame.jpg\" alt=\"Dixit_game_image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">3 - 8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">30m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T12:48:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Family</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/234190/unstable-unicorns\">Unstable Unicorns</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Build a Unicorn Army. Betray your friends. Unicorns are your friends now.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/35yKKOnpi5NTc4fCjrt9hqRA7qM=/fit-in/246x300/pic3912914.jpg\" alt=\"Unstable Unicorns\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2 - 8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">14</td>\n<td align=\"right\">30-45m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T12:05:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/machine-learning/crash-course/ml-intro\">Machine Learning Crash Course By Google</a> Machine Learning Crash Course features a series of lessons with video lectures, real-world case studies, and hands-on practice exercises.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T10:12:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/edu/python/\">Python Class By Google</a> This is a free class for people with a little bit of programming experience who want to learn Python. The class includes written materials, lecture videos, and lots of code exercises to practice Python coding.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T10:12:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"tmcw/awesome-geojson","categoryHTML":"<h3>data</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ustroetz.github.io/gimmeOSM/\">gimme OSM</a>: Fetch geojson file by openstreetmap id</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T10:12:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hbokh/awesome-saltstack","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.saltstack.com/\">SaltStack site</a> - Company website.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T09:58:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hbokh/awesome-saltstack","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hittaruki.info/post/vagrant-saltstack-tutorial/\">Vagrant &#x26; SaltStack Quickstart Tutorial</a> - Getting started with SaltStack and Vagrant.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T09:58:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hbokh/awesome-saltstack","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/erwindon/SaltGUI\">SaltGUI</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/erwindon/SaltGUI\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">285</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":285,\"repo\":\"erwindon/SaltGUI\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A web interface for managing SaltStack based infrastructure.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T09:58:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hbokh/awesome-saltstack","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://saltconf.com/\">SaltConf</a> - Annual user conference for SaltStack customers, users, partners, developers and community members.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T09:58:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"J2TEAM/awesome-AutoIt","categoryHTML":"<h2>UDF/Libraries</h2><h3>Graphics and image</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.autoitscript.fr/forum/viewtopic.php?f=21&#x26;t=9531\">Photoshop CS5 (by karime1)</a> - a new UDF to Control Photoshop CS5 Obj using AutoIt.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T09:11:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"markets/awesome-ruby","categoryHTML":"<h2>Email</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://4commerce-technologies-ag.github.io/midi-smtp-server/\">MidiSmtpServer</a> - The highly customizable ruby SMTP-Service library with builtin support for AUTH and SSL/STARTTLS, 8BITMIME and SMTPUTF8, IPv4 and IPv6 and more.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T07:50:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"brabadu/awesome-fonts","categoryHTML":"<h2>Free fonts</h2><h4>Fonts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/impallari/Libre-Franklin\">Libre Franklin</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/impallari/Libre-Franklin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">284</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":284,\"repo\":\"impallari/Libre-Franklin\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An interpretation and expansion based on Morris Fuller Benton’s 1912 classic.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T07:39:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Party</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/226322/s-question\">That's A Question﹗</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A great game to play with people you think you know. You take the role of squirrels asking each other questions as they climb up a mountain. Players assemble questions from tiles in their hands, asking each other things like \"Would you rather live in a world without pizza or fruit?\" or \"Would you rather write the Great American Novel or never have to sleep again?\" It's a good time for everyone, and the game has this nice, innocent charm to it. Even the manual is fun to read.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/HtERyYjSCmmOaczgGx_31xn_9EY=/fit-in/246x300/pic3643950.jpg\" alt=\"That&#x27;s A Question game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">3 - 6</td>\n<td align=\"right\">15</td>\n<td align=\"right\">30m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T07:12:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Party</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludo_(board_game)\">Ludo</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This board game can be played between minimum 2 to max 4 people of any age group. One of two dices can be used to move the tokens. The player whose all tokens reach home first is the winner. Player can kill other player's token by clashing his token to the same square. Other player's token goes back to house again. Some boards provides special squares where the token are safe and can’t be killed. Players can decide if they want a rule of getting additional turn to roll the dice upon getting 6. More exciting rules can be found on the Wikipedia link.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/Ludo-3.jpg/300px-Ludo-3.jpg\" alt=\"Ludo game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2 - 4</td>\n<td align=\"right\">4</td>\n<td align=\"right\">30-60m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T05:44:41.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategy</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YINSH\">YINSH</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Players start with five rings on the board. First player to remove 3 rings becomes the winner. Every time a ring is moved, it leaves a marker behind. Markers are white on one side and black on the other, and each time they are jumped they must be flipped. Once a player forms a row of 5 markers of their color, they can remove a ring. The challenge is each row you make brings you closer to victory-but also makes you weaker, because you have one fewer ring to play with.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/YINSH_in_Play.jpg/250px-YINSH_in_Play.jpg\" alt=\"YINSH game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2</td>\n<td align=\"right\">9</td>\n<td align=\"right\">30-60m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T04:16:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"willianjusten/awesome-audio-visualization","categoryHTML":"<h2>Experiments</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Teoxoy/audio-visualizer\">Audio Visualizer</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Teoxoy/audio-visualizer\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"Teoxoy/audio-visualizer\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An interesting web audio visualizer built with Pixi.js.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T03:41:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Strategy</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Game_of_Thrones_(board_game)\">Game of Thrones</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A Game of Thrones allows the players to take on the roles of several of the Great Houses vying for control of the Seven Kingdoms, including House Stark, House Lannister, House Baratheon, House Greyjoy, House Tyrell, and as of the expansion A Clash of Kings, House Martell. Players maneuver armies to secure support in the various regions that comprise the Seven Kingdoms, with the goal of capturing enough support to claim the Iron Throne. The basic gameplay mechanics are reminiscent of Diplomacy, especially in the order-giving process, though A Game of Thrones is significantly more complicated overall.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://awoiaf.westeros.org/thumb.php?f=Game-board-agot.png&#x26;width=250\" alt=\"Game of thrones boardgame image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">3 - 6</td>\n<td align=\"right\">12</td>\n<td align=\"right\">180-360m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T03:39:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Party</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://beziergames.com/products/one-night-ultimate-werewolf\">One Night Werewolf</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>One Night Ultimate Werewolf is a fast-paced game where everyone gets to be a different role. In the course of only one night and the following morning, the players will determine who among them is a werewolf...hopefully.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0740/4855/products/ONUW-BOX-COVER_250x250.jpg?v=1554841270\" alt=\"werewolf game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">3 - 10</td>\n<td align=\"right\">8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">10-15m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T03:17:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"josephmisiti/awesome-machine-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Javascript</h2><h4>General-Purpose Machine Learning</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ml5js/ml5-library\">ml5</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ml5js/ml5-library\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4808,\"repo\":\"ml5js/ml5-library\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Friendly machine learning for the web!</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T03:12:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In Portuguese</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://galeradorau.com.br/category/podcast/galera-do-rau/\">Galera do Rau</a> - Quatro professores, extremamente nerds, divertidos e com muita história pra contar.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T02:59:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In Portuguese</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cinemacomrapadura.com.br/cat/rapaduracast-podcast/\">Rapadura Cast</a> - Podcast da galera do Cinema com rapadura, considerado hoje referência sobre cultura pop no Brasil.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T02:59:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In Portuguese</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.redegeek.com.br/podcast/\">Rede Geek</a> - Podcast destinado ao público geek sobre diversos assuntos como, tecnologia, ciência, história e outros.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T02:59:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Party</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"http://www.worldofmunchkin.com/game/\">Munchkin</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Munchkin is the mega-hit card game about dungeon adventure ... with none of that stupid roleplaying stuff. You and your friends compete to kill monsters and grab magic items. And what magic items! Don the Horny Helmet and the Boots of Butt-Kicking. Wield the Staff of Napalm ... or maybe the Chainsaw of Bloody Dismemberment. Start by slaughtering the Potted Plant and the Drooling Slime, and work your way up to the Plutonium Dragon ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/e/ee/Munchkin_game_cover.jpg\" alt=\"Munchkin game image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">3 - 6</td>\n<td align=\"right\">10</td>\n<td align=\"right\">60-120m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2018-10-26T02:42:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JStumpp/awesome-android","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>GUI</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>